msgctxt "44"
msgid "How to Play Hidden Cricket"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56"
msgid "Unlike standard cricket, hidden cricket uses seven hidden numbers.\\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68"
msgid "The seven numbers are hidden at the start of the game and are not revealed until they are hit by a player. \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80"
msgid "Players who reveal a hidden number by hitting it for the first time receive an open bonus.\\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92"
msgid "Hitting numbers in the single ring counts as one hit, the double ring as two hits, and the triple ring as three hits.\\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "104"
msgid "Singles count as one hit, Doubles count as two hits, and Triples count as three hits.\\r\n"
" \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "116"
msgid "Three hits on a number closes it. \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "128"
msgid "The points from subsequent hits on a number you closed are added to your score.\\r\n"
" \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "140"
msgid "However, if your opponent closes that number as well, you will no longer get points when you hit it.\\r\n"
" \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "152"
msgid "When all rounds are concluded, the player with the higher score is declared the winner.\\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "164"
msgid "However, the game will also end if all numbers are closed before the end of the assigned number of rounds, and the player with the higher score is declared the winner.\\r\n"
" \\r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176"
msgid "I wish you the best of luck, sir."
msgstr ""

